KZN ANC Provincial Secretary, Mdumiseni Ntuli comments on political violence in the province. Courtesy of #DStv403 DURBAN - The ANC Youth League in eThekwini is calling for justice after one of its members was gunned down last week. Kingdom Gcabashe, a branch secretary, was killed outside a friend's house in Hammarsdale near Pietermaritzburg. READ: KZN whistleblower fighting for life after assassination attempt The ANC's provincial secretary Mdumiseni Ntuli said the party is concerned about losing lives to violence but stated they are not aware of any internal conflicts that would lead to killings. Ntuli said the police's investigation would hopefully yield more information on the motives behind the violence. Ntuli refused to be drawn on speculation on whether the killing was a political assassination.